<h2><a name="raise" id="raise">raise</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntax:
</p>
<pre class="c code c++" style="font-family:monospace;">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;csignal&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">int</span> raise<span class="br0">&#40;</span> <span class="kw4">int</span> signal <span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy0">;</span></pre>
<p>
The raise() function sends the specified signal to the program. Some signals:

</p>
<table class="inline">
	<tr class="row0">
		<th class="col0">Signal</th><th class="col1">Meaning</th>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row1">
		<td class="col0">SIGABRT </td><td class="col1">Termination error</td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row2">
		<td class="col0 leftalign">SIGFPE  </td><td class="col1">Floating pointer error</td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row3">
		<td class="col0 leftalign">SIGILL  </td><td class="col1">Bad instruction</td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row4">
		<td class="col0 leftalign">SIGINT  </td><td class="col1">User pressed CTRL-C</td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row5">
		<td class="col0">SIGSEGV </td><td class="col1">Illegal memory access</td>
	</tr>
	<tr class="row6">
		<td class="col0">SIGTERM </td><td class="col1">Terminate program</td>
	</tr>
</table>

<p>

The return value is zero upon success, nonzero on failure.
</p>

<p>
Related Topics: <a href="signal" class="wikilink1" title="c:other:signal">signal</a>
</p>

</div>
